-- Introduction --

Have you ever wondered how to prevent third parties from reading your messages? How can your app or web browser build a secure channel with a remote server? 
By secure mean that no one can read or alter the exchanged data; furthermore, we can be confident that we are connecting with the real server. Thanks to cryptography, these requirements are satisfied.

Cryptography lays the foundation for our digital world. While networking protocols have made it possible for devices spread across the globe to communicate, cryptography has made it possible to trust this communication.


